definition: head/hair style/the top/end/beginning or end/a stub/remnant/chief/boss/side/aspect/first/leading/classifier for pigs or livestock/CL:個|个[ge4]

sentences.english: Slurry is metered to the tine by a positive displacement pump.
sentences.chinese: 用一台容积泵测量泥浆尖头。

sentences.english: The pointed end of the stick pierced through its throat into its mouth.
sentences.chinese: 棍子的尖头从它的喉咙刺进它的嘴里。

sentences.english: Winkle pickers were the second generation rockers and very much the property of the early sixties generation.
sentences.chinese: 尖头鞋是第二代摇滚人的服饰，流行于六十年代早期。

sentences.english: There are many other designs of pin-tumbler besides the standard round or pointed tips.
sentences.chinese: 除了标准的圆头和尖头珠子外还有很多不同种的设计。

sentences.english: But not a single Clovis point has turned up in Siberia.
sentences.chinese: 但是在西伯利亚连一块克洛维斯尖头都没有发现。

sentences.english: One end of a pencil is tapered off to a point.
sentences.chinese: 铅笔的一端逐渐尖细成一尖头。

sentences.english: Sporangium was born in stem top, long in shape, no stalk, a small pointed.
sentences.chinese: 孢子囊生于茎顶，长圆形，无柄，具小尖头。

sentences.english: One end of the stick tapers down to a point.
sentences.chinese: 木棍的一头渐渐变细成一个尖头。

sentences.english: Large deciduous tree of the pacific coast having deeply parted bristle-tipped leaves.
sentences.chinese: 太平洋沿岸高大的落叶树，叶深裂，具刚毛尖头。

sentences.english: Pointy shoes are the fashion this year.
sentences.chinese: 尖头鞋是今年的流行款式。

sentences.english: The flagpole tapered off to a point.
sentences.chinese: 那支旗竿逐渐变细成尖头。

sentences.english: The tooth of roll crusher is pointed, used for crushing coal, coke and limestone.
sentences.chinese: 破碎机的齿轮为尖头状，用于碎煤，焦炭和石灰石。

sentences.english: Use arrows to show steps in a process or direction of movement.
sentences.chinese: 使用尖头来表示移动方向或者过程中的步骤。

sentences.english: A prong on an implement such as a fork or pitchfork.
sentences.chinese: 尖齿叉子或干草叉等工具上的尖头。

sentences.english: A pointed object, such as an ice pick, a goad, or a thorn.
sentences.chinese: 尖刺尖头物，如冰戳，尖棒或荆棘。

sentences.english: With his pointed shoes and his bells.
sentences.chinese: 穿着他的尖头鞋和他的铃铛。
